<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-173-968  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 173 968.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>The Journal of Systems and Software  Jan 1990 v11 n1 p45(8).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>On the management of long-living transactions. (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brahmadathan, K.; Ramarao, K.V.S.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Long-living transactions are those transactions that exist in thesystem for relatively long periods of time.andP;  Because of theirspecial nature, these transactions cause scheduling difficulties.andO;Traditional concurrency control methods are unsatisfactory fortheir management.andP;  In this paper, we propose methods to handlelong-living transactions efficiently.andP;  Our algorithm extends someof the previous works on this problem in several important ways.andO;We first propose several performance criteria to be satisfied byany solution and then provide an efficient solution for themanagement of long-living transactions.andP;  In this process, weidentify several aspects to the problem and suggest approaches tothese issues.andP;  Extensions to the case of a multitude of longtransactions and distributed data base systems are considered.andP;  Weshow that attractive solutions are possible in these situations.andO;(Reprinted by permission of the publisher)andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Programming InstructionSoftware DesignAlgorithmsOn-Line Transaction ProcessingDistributed Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>